Absolutely — here’s the **final combined HTML + CSS package** ready for review or sandbox testing.  
It keeps every ethical and accessibility element in place: the “not therapy” banner remains visible, ARIA roles and alt‑text are clear, and the global helpline is permanent in the footer.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Immediate Support & Calming Prompts</title>

  <style>
    :root {
      --banner-bg: #5FB6B0;
      --footer-bg: #E35B5B;
      --text-light: #F4F4F4;
      --text-dark: #333;
      --link-color: #1E73BE;
      --max-width: 600px;
      --focus-outline: 2px solid #1E73BE;
    }

    /* Reduced motion */
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      * { transition: none !important; animation-duration: 0ms !important; }
    }

    /* Dark mode adjustment */
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      body { background: #242424; color: var(--text-light); }
      header.sticky-banner, footer[role="contentinfo"] { color: var(--text-dark); }
    }

    /* Basic structure */
    body {
      font-family: "Open Sans", "Roboto", sans-serif;
      color: var(--text-dark);
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    header.sticky-banner {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 10;
      width: 100%;
      background: var(--banner-bg);
      color: var(--text-light);
      text-align: center;
      padding: 0.5em;
    }

    footer[role="contentinfo"] {
      position: sticky;
      bottom: 0;
      z-index: 10;
      width: 100%;
      background: var(--footer-bg);
      color: var(--text-light);
      text-align: center;
      padding: 0.5em;
    }

    main {
      max-width: var(--max-width);
      padding: 1em;
    }

    a:focus, button:focus {
      outline: var(--focus-outline);
      outline-offset: 2px;
    }

    dialog[open] {
      border: none;
      padding: 1em;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      width: 90%;
      max-width: var(--max-width);
    }

    .skip-link {
      position: absolute;
      left: -999px;
      top: auto;
    }
    .skip-link:focus {
      position: static;
      margin: 0.5em;
      background: var(--link-color);
      color: var(--text-light);
      padding: 0.25em 0.5em;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <!-- Fixed banner -->
  <header role="banner" class="sticky-banner" aria-label="Self‑soothing information">
    🕊️ Self‑soothing ideas — not therapy
    <a href="#main" class="skip-link">Skip to calming ideas</a>
  </header>

  <!-- Main header and disclaimer -->
  <section id="intro">
    <h1>Immediate Support & Calming Prompts</h1>
    <p>Short grounding ideas for tense moments.</p>
    <button id="infoBtn" aria-haspopup="dialog" aria-controls="disclaimerModal">ℹ️ Info</button>
  </section>

  <!-- Disclaimer modal -->
  <dialog id="disclaimerModal" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="modalTitle">
    <h2 id="modalTitle">About these prompts</h2>
    <p>
      These are quick grounding ideas for emotional support.
      They are not professional advice or therapy.
      If you ever feel unsafe, please reach out for help at
      <a href="https://findahelpline.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">findahelpline.com</a>.
    </p>
    <button id="closeModal">Close</button>
  </dialog>

  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav aria-label="Choose your state">
    <p>Pick what fits → 🌿 Panic | 🌧️ Sadness | 🌀 Racing Thoughts | ❄️ Numbness</p>
  </nav>

  <!-- Main content blocks -->
  <main id="main">
    <section aria-labelledby="panicTitle">
      <h2 id="panicTitle">🌿 Panic</h2>
      <p>Slow breath (4 in, 6 out). Feel one point of contact — feet or chair.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="sadnessTitle">
      <h2 id="sadnessTitle">🌧️ Sadness</h2>
      <p>Hand on chest, notice breath. Sip water or rest briefly.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="racingTitle">
      <h2 id="racingTitle">🌀 Racing Thoughts</h2>
      <p>Say or write one thought, pause, breathe again before the next.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="numbTitle">
      <h2 id="numbTitle">❄️ Numbness</h2>
      <p>Touch one texture — fabric, air, wall — and stay with that sense.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- Persistent footer -->
  <footer role="contentinfo" aria-label="Crisis helplines">
    🌍 Free international crisis support:
    <a href="https://findahelpline.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">findahelpline.com</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

Open this in any browser or sandbox—it will show a static version with the “self‑soothing ideas — not therapy” banner at the top and the helpline always visible at the bottom.  
From here, your developer only needs to wire up the tiny script for the modal’s open/close focus handling before accessibility testing starts.
